                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A4e/561: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Delegation</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-03-03T15:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 3, 1926—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 3—9:43 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Conference 26. British delegates inactive, say they are waiting instructions from
                    their Government respecting the attitude of Chinese provinces toward Conference
                    and proposed treaty. We told them we proposed to proceed with negotiations
                    irrespective disturbed conditions; that we were bound to effectuate Washington
                    Treaty and thought it advantageous that powers should endeavor to get in accord
                    on general tariff policy toward China, then if China went to pieces before
                    treaty ratified, responsibility of disintegration would not be on powers. Under
                    all the circumstances we believe we should diligently proceed with negotiations
                    and encourage others to do so.</p>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Am</hi>[<hi rend="smallcaps">erican</hi>] <hi
                        rend="smallcaps">Tar</hi> [<hi rend="smallcaps">iff</hi>] <hi
                        rend="smallcaps">Del</hi>[<hi rend="smallcaps">egation</hi>]</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
